Brazil show irks Pele | Beijing 2008 | Sports | The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata)
                                                                                                                                                                                                             Brazil show irks Pele
            Beijing bytes                
	Football legend Pele Thursday criticised Brazils Olympic campaign which ended in a demoralising 3-0 quarter final defeat to bitter rivals Argentina. I think Argentina were better prepared than Brazil, said Pele. Once again, Brazil couldnt win the gold medal. Its not good for us but this is what happens in football...         
	Horses banned         
	Four horses have been banned from competing in Thursdays Olympic Games jumping competition for doping, the International Equestrian Federation (FEI) announced. The horses had been suspended after testing positive for a prohibited substance, the FEI said in a statement.         
	Golden stunt         
	The head of the Puma sportswear brand Thursday denied the company had urged athletics star Usain Bolt to display his golden running shoes after his Olympic triumphs. Bolt ruffled some feathers by removing his customised Puma footwear and kissing them in front of photographers and TV crews.                                                                                                                            
